This is the README file for CPANPLUS::Shell::Default::Plugins::Diff,
a CPANPLUS shell plugin for displaying differences between released 
modules.

Please refer to 'perldoc CPANPLUS::Shell::Default::Plugins::Diff' 
after installation for details.

#####################################################################

* Description

CPANPLUS::Shell::Default::Plugins::Diff

    This plugin allows you to diff 2 versions of modules and see 
    what code changes have taken place.

#####################################################################

* Installation

CPANPLUS::Shell::Default::Plugins::Diff follows the standard perl 
module install process:

perl Makefile.PL
make
make test
make install

The module uses no C or XS parts, so no c-compiler is required.

